DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A benign or malignant pathologic structure in any part of the body, resulting from a neoplastic accumulation of cells._Greater or bigger in amount, extent, or size._A tube through which the blood circulates in the body.  Blood vessels include a network of arteries, arterioles, capillaries, venules, and veins._Happening or arising or located outside or beyond some limits, or especially, some surface._Of or pertaining to the kidney._The tissue that constitutes the essential part of an organ as contrasted with e.g., connective tissue and blood vessels._The final result of a determination of the value, significance, or extent of.
